gujarati.context:
Here are the translations:

They came to Ahmedabad with mercy, the crowd was delighted; 
They came as companions in good company, their beauty did not decay thus.

Sat sangee sankhyayogi sant, utarya bhakta ne bhagavant;
Karyan sundar saaran bhojan, jamya janane bhavai jivan.

(Note: I've translated the couplet directly without adding any extra words)

Here is the translation:

After four corners have been washed away, they sit above like this; 
You have shown me eternal vision, O Lord, my soul has become your flame.

Here is the translation:

Bring them by force if you must, see their souls; 
It comes forth those of old, for showing mercy's sight.

Here is the translation:

He was a festival alone in a group, kept divine love within; 
Every day, darshan, donation, did much devotion to God.

Ved vidhiye utsav karee, aapyaa dan pachii hars bhari;
Ghoordee palan charma ne asi, aapie padhee mahishi.

The Vedas ordain the festival to be celebrated, and then joy is filled after giving alms; 
Unbroken skin of the mare, it was given along with the cow.
